INTRODUCTION AND READING OF BILLS

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to notices of violation issued by the department of sanitation for illegal postings.
EventItemMatterName: Notices of violation issued by the department of sanitation for illegal postings.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to trash receptacles placed out for collection by the department of sanitation.
EventItemMatterName: Trash receptacles placed out for collection by the department of sanitation.

EventItemActionText: This Introduction was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Housing and Buildings
EventItemTitle: A Local Law to amend the administrative code of the city of New York, in relation to prohibiting persons receiving public funds or subsidies to be placed in buildings with a history of tenant harassment.
EventItemMatterName: Prohibiting persons receiving public funds or subsidies to be placed in buildings with a history of tenant harassment.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Immigration
EventItemTitle: Resolution urging the United States Congress to pass and the President to sign the Protect Citizens and Residents from Unlawful Detention Act and the Strong Safe Treatment, Avoiding Needless Deaths, and Abuse Reduction in the Detention System (STANDARDS) Act, two bills that will reform the U.S. immigration detention system.
EventItemMatterName: Protect Citizens and Residents from Unlawful Detention Act and the Strong Safe Treatment, Avoiding Needless Deaths, and Abuse Reduction in the Detention System (STANDARDS) Act.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Sanitation and Solid Waste Management
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to introduce, and the Governor to sign, legislation which would provide tax incentives for food-service businesses to use environmentally-friendly alternatives to disposable food ware made from Styrofoam and other non-recyclable or non-biodegradable materials.
EventItemMatterName: Provide tax incentives for food-service businesses to use environmentally-friendly alternatives to disposable food ware made from Styrofoam and other non-recyclable or non-biodegradable materials.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Aging
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to pass S.1574/A.2656, The Caregiver’s Assistance Act.
EventItemMatterName: The Caregiver’s Assistance Act. (S.1574/A.2656)

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Governmental Operations
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling upon the New York State Legislature to amend section 6-134 of the New York State Election Law in order to extend from three to seven business days a candidate’s time to cure any violations on submitted petitions, and to allow voters to sign multiple petitions without consequence of disqualification.
EventItemMatterName: Extend from 3 to 7 business days a candidate’s time to cure any violations on submitted petitions, and to allow voters to sign multiple petitions without consequence of disqualification.

EventItemActionText: This Resolution was Referred to Comm by Council to the Committee on Waterfronts
EventItemTitle: Resolution calling on the States of New York and New Jersey to enact legislation that  dissolves the Waterfront Commission of New York Harbor and calling on the United States Congress to grant its consent.
EventItemMatterName: Dissolves the Waterfront Commission of New York Harbor and calling on the United States Congress to grant its consent.
